#Text=The Dallas Mavericks ( 16 - 6 ) defeated the Milwaukee Bucks ( 11 - 11 ) 125 - 102 on Sunday at the American Airlines Center in Dallas .
#Text=The Mavericks used their superior shooting in this matchup , as they went 58 percent from the field and 39 percent from the three - point line .
#Text=The Bucks in comparison shot 50 percent from the floor and only 27 percent from beyond the arc .
#Text=The Mavericks also forced the Bucks into 19 turnovers , which only added to Dallas ' advantage in the 23 - point victory .
#Text=The trio of Chandler Parsons , Dirk Nowitzki and Monta Ellis really killed the Bucks .
#Text=Parsons could n't miss and went 11 - for - 14 from the field and 4 - for - 6 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 28 points .
#Text=He 's averaged just under 15 points up to this point , so it was a nice surprise for the Mavericks to get the type of production they 've been looking for all season from him .
#Text=Nowitzki shot nearly as well as Parsons and finished with 21 points ( 8 - 12 FG , 1 - 4 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) and four rebounds .
#Text=He struggled to only 10 points ( 2 - 10 FG ) on Friday against the Suns , so it was a nice bounce back game for him .
#Text=Ellis had 19 points ( 7 - 13 FG , 1 - 5 3Pt , 4 - 6 FT ) and four assists as the third member of the starting lineup to reach double figures .
#Text=In only five minutes off the bench , Richard Jefferson was able to go a perfect 4 - 4 from the field and 2 - for - 2 from beyond the arc to score 10 points .
#Text=It was good enough to lead the bench in scoring .
#Text=The Bucks had all five starters reach double figures in points , but just did n't play enough defense to keep them close .
#Text=Giannis Antetokounmpo led the team with 18 points ( 8 - 11 FG , 2 - 3 FT ) and four rebounds .
#Text=It was the most points he 's had in the last seven games , so the Bucks will hope it can boost his confidence even more .
#Text=Brandon Knight had 16 points of his own , but did most of his damage from the free throw line where he went a perfect 7 - for - 7 .
#Text=He 's done most of the scoring for the Bucks in the last two weeks , and it looks like it may continue .
#Text=Rookie Jabari Parker shot 7 - for - 12 from the field to score 15 points , while also chipping in five rebounds .
#Text=He 's now averaging 12 points and 6 rebounds on the year .
#Text=Zaza Puchulia gave a good push off the bench and fnished with 13 points and eight rebounds .
#Text=The Mavericks ' next game will be on the road against the Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday , while the Bucks will travel to Oklahoma City to play the Thunder on Tuesday .
